Gupta Publicity May Jeopardize India Steel Deal, Bus. Day Says

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-03-04T05:54:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/gupta-publicity-may-jeopardize-india-steel-deal-bus-day-says.html
The Gupta family is concerned
adverse publicity concerning their relationship with President  Jacob Zuma  may jeopardize a 21 billion-rand proposed plan with
the Steel Authority of India Ltd. to build a steel plant in  South Africa , Business Day reported, citing family patriarch
Ajay Gupta.  The Gupta’s Oakbay Trust holds stakes in Lazarus Zim’s
Afripalm group of companies and Afripalm Horizons signed the
memorandum with Steel Authority of India, the Johannesburg-based
newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  